## 📋 Pre-Ingestion Compliance Checklist

### Before Processing Any Third-Party Document

- [ ] **Source identification**: Is the document's origin and authorship known?
- [ ] **License check**: Is there an explicit license or public domain declaration?
- [ ] **AI opt-out scan**: Run `CopyrightChecker` on first 3,000 chars for opt-out patterns
- [ ] **Reproduction rights scan**: Check for "All Rights Reserved" and similar phrases
- [ ] **Scope validation**: What will the extracted content be used for?
- [ ] **Metadata logging**: Record `filename`, `source_url`, `declared_license`, `copyright_status`

### During LLM Processing

- [ ] **Instruction injection**: Include copyright constraint in LLM system prompt for RESTRICTED docs
- [ ] **Output validation**: Verify LLM output contains no verbatim excerpts from RESTRICTED docs
- [ ] **Citation enforcement**: Every extracted rule/plan must reference its source document
- [ ] **Confidence tracking**: Log confidence scores for traceability

### Post-Processing

- [ ] **Audit trail**: Log `processing_id`, `copyright_status`, and guardrail results per document
- [ ] **Status update**: Update `documents.copyright_status` in the database
- [ ] **Blocked document notification**: Alert Admin for all BLOCKED documents

---

## 🚨 Red Flags — Stop Processing Immediately

**Patterns that require BLOCKED classification:**

- `"expressly prohibits"` + `"AI"` or `"artificial intelligence"`
- `"text and data mining"` + `"prohibited"` or `"not permitted"`
- `"s'oppose expressément"` + `"intelligence artificielle"` (French AFNOR pattern)
- `"TDM opt-out"` or `"AI opt-out"`
- `"no AI training"`, `"no AI processing"`, `"no machine learning"`
- Any machine-readable robots.txt or HTML meta `<meta name="robots" content="noai">`

---

## 🔄 Classification Review

### When to Re-Classify

- When a document is updated or replaced with a new version
- When the rightsholder updates their license terms
- When regulatory guidance on DSM Art. 4 opt-out is updated
- Annually for all documents in active use
